In occupational therapy, students have learned how light can be used as a tool during peace or relaxation time. Here, she's created a lantern from a milk carton and a string of holiday lights.

You can even experiment using multiple cartons and strands to create a small or big display!

post_text:
You have to check this out, #WeAre917 fans! ü•≥

A grant from Education Minnesota Foundation for Excellence in Teaching and Learning was awarded to Mary Callister, PE/DAPE teacher at Lebanon Education Center, to create a sensory hallway for students.

Sensory paths are designed to help children use their bodies and environment to calm themselves. They use their muscles, breathing, and spatial awareness to completely absorb themselves in the sensory path. It helps kids reset and be refreshed. Stickers and stencils were purchased through Fit and Fun Playscapes.

Thank you, Mary, for obtaining this grant!

A grant from Education Minnesota Foundation for Excellence in Teaching and Learning was awarded to Mary Callister, PE/DAPE teacher at Lebanon Education Center, to create a sensory hallway for students.

Sensory paths are designed to help children use their bodies and environment to calm themselves. They use their muscles, breathing, and spatial awareness to completely absorb themselves in the sensory path. It helps kids reset and be refreshed. Stickers and stencils were purchased through Fit and Fun Playscapes.

Thank you, Mary, for obtaining this grant!
